WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:07.670
♪♪

00:07.670 --> 00:10.000
Hey, Mom, look what I made you
at school yesterday.

00:11.040 --> 00:13.420
Oh, it's beautiful.

00:14.250 --> 00:15.790
Give me a minute
to figure out what it is

00:15.790 --> 00:17.790
and I'll tell you
how much I love it.

00:17.790 --> 00:19.500
It's a plastic-bag
dryer.

00:19.500 --> 00:22.290
It's so you can wash
and reuse plastic baggies.

00:22.290 --> 00:24.790
What prissy mom
came up with that idea?

00:24.790 --> 00:26.210
Dad.

00:26.210 --> 00:27.750
We had fun
making them.

00:27.750 --> 00:29.170
You know
what else would be fun?

00:29.170 --> 00:30.500
If you stopped
coming up with stuff

00:30.500 --> 00:31.750
that makes
more work for me.

00:31.750 --> 00:34.210
Katie, I'm head of the school's
green committee.

00:34.210 --> 00:36.210
It's important that we up
our recycling game.

00:36.210 --> 00:38.000
Am I still supposed to
pretend recycling is real

00:38.000 --> 00:39.380
in front of Anna-Kat?

00:39.380 --> 00:40.420
She's 10, Greg.

00:40.420 --> 00:42.210
Hey, Mr. and Mrs. A.
Hey.

00:42.210 --> 00:43.790
I'm here to pick up Taylor
for school.

00:43.790 --> 00:45.420
Now that
it's my second senior year,

00:45.420 --> 00:46.880
Taylor and I
are in the same class.

00:46.880 --> 00:48.790
Fingers crossed I don't end up
with Anna-Kat.

00:48.790 --> 00:49.920
I love your hair today,
Mom.

00:49.920 --> 00:51.420
Thanks, Taylor!

00:51.420 --> 00:53.000
Look at that.

00:53.000 --> 00:54.960
She gave you a compliment
and didn't ask for money.

00:54.960 --> 00:56.670
[ Gasps ]
I know.

00:56.670 --> 00:58.210
We might finally
be entering

00:58.210 --> 01:00.080
the mother-daughter
friend phase.

01:00.080 --> 01:02.120
We could go
to Mardi Gras together.

01:02.120 --> 01:03.710
But she's not gonna get
more beads than me.

01:03.710 --> 01:05.790
I have great news.

01:05.790 --> 01:07.330
I got an interview
at Teen Help Line.

01:07.330 --> 01:08.620
What's Teen Help Line?

01:08.620 --> 01:10.210
Oh, it's this
volunteer organization

01:10.210 --> 01:12.710
where teens call to talk
to peers about their problems.

01:12.710 --> 01:14.170
It's a great way
to impress Harvard

01:14.170 --> 01:15.710
now that
I can't do ballet.
Katie: Huh.

01:15.710 --> 01:17.580
Don't you need empathy
for that?

01:17.580 --> 01:19.500
[ Door opens ]
[ Scoffs ]
I've gotten this far without it.

01:19.500 --> 01:21.000
[ Door closes ]
Plus,
they give you a script,

01:21.000 --> 01:23.420
and if anyone starts to cry
or something gross like that,

01:23.420 --> 01:24.920
I'll just pretend
I got disconnected.

01:24.920 --> 01:27.460
They'll be lucky
to have you.

01:27.460 --> 01:29.330
♪♪

01:29.330 --> 01:31.880
She wants me to wash out
plastic bags.

01:31.880 --> 01:33.210
What the hell for?

01:33.210 --> 01:35.620
I barely have time
to wash my own damn self.

01:35.620 --> 01:37.620
Ugh. Marigold wants me
to wash out those bags, too.

01:37.620 --> 01:39.880
It's really caused a rift
between me and the housekeeper.

01:39.880 --> 01:41.120
She just thinks

01:41.120 --> 01:42.460
the rich lady has found
another way to torture her.

01:42.460 --> 01:44.460
Just give the woman
her passport back.

01:44.460 --> 01:45.830
No.

01:45.830 --> 01:47.420
The only kid not bugging me
is Taylor.

01:47.420 --> 01:49.620
She even complimented me
for no reason this morning.

01:49.620 --> 01:51.290
Mm.
Uh-oh.

01:51.290 --> 01:52.540
What?

01:52.540 --> 01:54.210
No kid is nice
for no reason, Katie.

01:54.210 --> 01:56.080
She's clearly
hiding something from you.

01:56.080 --> 01:57.540
You think?

01:57.540 --> 01:59.250
Marigold told me
I smelled nice the other day,

01:59.250 --> 02:00.540
so I flipped her
upside down

02:00.540 --> 02:02.750
and shook five Pixie Stix
out of her pockets.

02:02.750 --> 02:03.920
A mother knows,
Katie.

02:03.920 --> 02:05.210
You're right.

02:05.210 --> 02:07.000
I'm going to
search Taylor's room.

02:07.000 --> 02:09.330
Okay, you're going
about this the wrong way.

02:09.330 --> 02:11.830
You should be the kind of mom
she'd want to come to.

02:11.830 --> 02:13.790
The last thing you should
be doing is snooping.

02:13.790 --> 02:15.120
It's a complete
breach of trust.

02:15.120 --> 02:17.000
No,
you're right.

02:17.000 --> 02:18.380
It's the wrong thing
to do.

02:18.380 --> 02:19.580
Angela's wrong.

02:19.580 --> 02:22.120
Snooping feels
absolutely right.

02:22.120 --> 02:23.710
It's a good thing
her room is so messy.

02:23.710 --> 02:25.080
We don't have to
put anything back.

02:25.080 --> 02:27.420
This is suspicious.

02:27.420 --> 02:29.120
What?
A book.

02:29.120 --> 02:31.540
In Taylor's room.

02:31.540 --> 02:33.500
Oh.

02:33.500 --> 02:35.710
Oh, my.
What "oh, my"?

02:35.710 --> 02:37.420
Well, it's a prescription
for birth-control pills.

02:38.620 --> 02:39.880
In her name.

02:39.880 --> 02:41.960
Oh.

02:41.960 --> 02:44.040
I feel sick.

02:45.420 --> 02:46.830
What are you doing?

02:46.830 --> 02:48.330
If there are drugs in here,
I'm gonna find them,

02:48.330 --> 02:49.670
'cause you could really
use some right now.

02:49.670 --> 02:51.670
♪♪

02:54.500 --> 02:56.750
♪♪

02:56.750 --> 02:57.830
[ Chatter ]

03:01.460 --> 03:02.880
What are you
in the mood for today, Franklin?

03:02.880 --> 03:04.540
The mac-n-cheese
looks good.

03:04.540 --> 03:06.710
Well, I'm allergic to dairy,
cheese, and pasta.

03:06.710 --> 03:08.170
Is there any of that
in there?

03:08.170 --> 03:10.330
[ Sighs ]
Hey!

03:10.330 --> 03:13.380
The lunch lady's
using disposable plates.

03:13.380 --> 03:14.380
Excuse me --

03:14.380 --> 03:15.790
Mac-n-cheese
or fish sticks?

03:15.790 --> 03:16.960
Mac-n-cheese, please.

03:16.960 --> 03:18.460
He'll have
the fish sticks.

03:19.620 --> 03:22.170
And also, why aren't you using
washable plates?

03:22.170 --> 03:24.460
The plastic ones are just gonna
end up in a landfill.

03:24.460 --> 03:26.500
Tell somebody
who gives a dink.

03:26.500 --> 03:28.460
You can't talk that way.
There's a lady present.

03:28.460 --> 03:30.000
What are you
gonna do about it?

03:30.000 --> 03:31.540
Eat mac-n-cheese,
break out in hives,

03:31.540 --> 03:32.920
and throw up
all over your floor.

03:34.670 --> 03:36.080
Knock yourself out.

03:36.080 --> 03:37.330
[ Door opens ]

03:37.330 --> 03:38.460
Dad!

03:38.460 --> 03:39.880
Yeah.
[ Sighs ]

03:39.880 --> 03:41.040
[ Door closes ]

03:41.040 --> 03:43.500
The lunch lady won't use
real plates.

03:43.500 --> 03:45.670
She uses
plastic ones

03:45.670 --> 03:47.080
and then just
throws them away.

03:47.080 --> 03:48.170
What?

03:48.170 --> 03:50.420
Not in my school.

03:50.420 --> 03:53.000
I tried talking to her,
but she won't listen.

03:53.000 --> 03:54.790
This is a job
for the recycling committee.

03:54.790 --> 03:56.750
Bill Doty and I
will take it from here.

03:56.750 --> 03:58.790
Sounds like the lunch lady
just needs to be educated.

03:58.790 --> 04:00.920
Yeah,
and if that doesn't work,

04:00.920 --> 04:02.330
we'll recycle her face!

04:02.330 --> 04:04.170
You get more like your mother
every day.

04:04.170 --> 04:06.920
[ Chuckles ]

04:06.920 --> 04:10.290
♪♪

04:10.290 --> 04:12.540
Hi, Mom.
I like your shirt today.

04:12.540 --> 04:16.080
Liar! You don't like
anything about me!

04:16.080 --> 04:18.170
I found this.

04:18.170 --> 04:19.790
Where did you
get this?!

04:19.790 --> 04:21.500
You went in my room?!

04:21.500 --> 04:23.500
If we're talking about
who's going in where,

04:23.500 --> 04:25.920
I think there's a bigger
conversation to be had.

04:25.920 --> 04:28.210
Okay, Mom, calm down.
We haven't done it yet.

04:28.210 --> 04:29.500
But at some point, we will.
Right, Trip?

04:32.250 --> 04:34.380
I just came in
for apple juice.

04:34.380 --> 04:36.420
You promised me you were
going to come to me first

04:36.420 --> 04:38.750
when you were
thinking of having sex.

04:38.750 --> 04:40.580
I never
was really gonna do that.
Double liar!

04:40.580 --> 04:42.380
Well, you're a snoop!
I don't trust you anymore!

04:42.380 --> 04:45.000
I don't know
if I can trust you anymore!

04:46.290 --> 04:49.040
I'm smelling
some tension.

04:49.040 --> 04:51.170
Maybe Teen Help Line
can offer some support.

04:52.710 --> 04:54.580
"Hi.
I'm glad you called.

04:54.580 --> 04:55.580
This is a safe place
for you to express" --

04:55.580 --> 04:56.920
Let me see that.

05:01.210 --> 05:03.000
[ Script clatters ]
[ Scoffs ]
If you're ever wondering

05:03.000 --> 05:05.040
where my lack of empathy
comes from...

05:05.040 --> 05:07.000
Give me back
my prescription

05:07.000 --> 05:08.580
that you stole
from my room!

05:08.580 --> 05:10.790
Well,
your room is in my house,

05:10.790 --> 05:14.210
so I get to do this.

05:14.210 --> 05:15.460
Well,
it doesn't matter.

05:15.460 --> 05:17.120
I'll just get Angela
to take me to the doctor again.

05:18.790 --> 05:19.830
What?!

05:19.830 --> 05:21.380
Angela took you?!

05:23.120 --> 05:24.210
[ Door slams ]

05:24.210 --> 05:29.960
♪♪

05:29.960 --> 05:31.960
I played laser tag
last night.

05:31.960 --> 05:33.080
You ever been?

05:35.380 --> 05:37.170
There was a 12-year-old
who covered his target.

05:38.830 --> 05:40.120
It's against the rules.

05:40.120 --> 05:41.920
Get out.

05:41.920 --> 05:43.420
Thank you.

05:43.420 --> 05:44.710
♪♪

05:48.580 --> 05:50.250
♪♪

05:50.250 --> 05:52.330
I cannot believe
you took my daughter

05:52.330 --> 05:54.750
to get birth control
without asking me.

05:54.750 --> 05:57.250
Okay. [ Scoffs ]
You have to understand.

05:57.250 --> 05:58.790
When Taylor came to me

05:58.790 --> 06:00.210
and asked me
to take her to the doctor,

06:00.210 --> 06:02.210
I was afraid
that if I said no,

06:02.210 --> 06:03.880
she would start having
unprotected sex,

06:03.880 --> 06:05.120
and I knew
you wouldn't want that.

06:05.120 --> 06:07.750
But I should have been the one
to take her.

06:07.750 --> 06:09.750
I'm her mother.
But would you
have taken her?

06:09.750 --> 06:12.210
No!
I am her mother!
See?

06:12.210 --> 06:14.460
This is why Taylor didn't
go to you, because you
always shut her down.

06:14.460 --> 06:17.830
But when Taylor came to you,
you should have come to me.
She asked me not to.

06:17.830 --> 06:20.420
She asked me not to go to school
in my pajama bottoms!

06:20.420 --> 06:22.290
You don't have to listen
to a teenager!

06:22.290 --> 06:24.120
Doris?
You want to weigh in here?

06:24.120 --> 06:26.250
Yeah, Doris, weigh in.
Tell her I'm right.

06:26.250 --> 06:27.790
I'll do
what I always do, okay?

06:27.790 --> 06:29.880
I'll side with each of you
behind the other's back.

06:29.880 --> 06:31.830
That way,
I stay the favorite.

06:31.830 --> 06:33.080
[ Sighs ]

06:33.080 --> 06:34.460
I've got to
get to court,

06:34.460 --> 06:36.750
where people argue
and make sense.

06:36.750 --> 06:37.790
This conversation
is not over.

06:37.790 --> 06:39.830
Angela, this conversation
is not --

06:39.830 --> 06:42.330
She can't hear me, but this
conversation is not over.

06:42.330 --> 06:44.580
♪♪

06:44.580 --> 06:47.170
Now, before we start the show,
I'd like to introduce my friend

06:47.170 --> 06:49.830
and the sunshine
on my compost pile,

06:49.830 --> 06:52.500
Mr. Bill Doty!

06:52.500 --> 06:54.670
[ Imitates cheering ]

06:54.670 --> 06:56.500
Let's get on
with this.

06:56.500 --> 06:59.080
I only get a 48-minute lunch
at Foot Locker.
Hmm.

06:59.080 --> 07:01.540
Did somebody hire the two
worst strippers in Westport?

07:01.540 --> 07:03.500
'Cause I didn't.

07:03.500 --> 07:05.380
Well, we're gonna do
a little show for you

07:05.380 --> 07:07.790
that will not only
rock your world...

07:07.790 --> 07:09.670
But save it!
...but save it!

07:09.670 --> 07:12.210
We're gonna lay some knowledge
on you about recycling

07:12.210 --> 07:14.250
and have a little bit of fun
along the way.

07:14.250 --> 07:17.500
Join us now, somewhere on
an American coastline.

07:17.500 --> 07:21.330
♪♪

07:21.330 --> 07:23.380
The beach is a perfect place
to have my lunch.

07:23.380 --> 07:25.000
♪♪

07:25.000 --> 07:27.420
Well, I don't need
this plastic wrapper anymore.

07:27.420 --> 07:29.210
Guess I'll throw it
in the ocean.

07:29.210 --> 07:31.500
What harm
could it possibly do?

07:31.500 --> 07:33.120
[ Dramatic music playing ]

07:33.120 --> 07:35.750
I hope
you enjoyed your lunch.

07:35.750 --> 07:37.750
It cost me my life.

07:37.750 --> 07:40.710
[ Imitates
dolphin squawking ]

07:40.710 --> 07:44.120
♪♪

07:44.120 --> 07:45.670
We promise
to all dolphins,

07:45.670 --> 07:46.790
we'll make sure

07:46.790 --> 07:48.750
no one throws plastic
in their home again.

07:48.750 --> 07:50.960
Go on, go on.

07:50.960 --> 07:52.170
♪♪

07:52.170 --> 07:54.580
And...scene.

07:54.580 --> 08:01.120
♪♪

08:01.120 --> 08:02.580
I'm gonna tell you
the same thing

08:02.580 --> 08:05.580
I told the touring company
of "The Sound of Music" --

08:05.580 --> 08:07.670
this sucks, and I'm outta here.

08:07.670 --> 08:09.000
[ Slurps ]

08:12.920 --> 08:14.040
She doesn't seem moved.

08:14.040 --> 08:15.170
Mm.
Maybe she's in pain.

08:15.170 --> 08:16.670
I mean,
look at those feet.

08:16.670 --> 08:18.000
She's wearing
a size 9,

08:18.000 --> 08:19.210
and she's clearly
a 9 1/2.

08:20.960 --> 08:23.710
Sorry, it's hard to leave work
at the office sometimes.
Sure.

08:23.710 --> 08:26.290
♪♪

08:26.290 --> 08:28.580
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

08:29.620 --> 08:31.710
Oliver: Whoa.

08:31.710 --> 08:33.460
It looks like you could use
someone to talk to.

08:33.460 --> 08:34.880
Yeah,
that would be nice.

08:34.880 --> 08:36.210
Oh, great.

08:36.210 --> 08:38.830
Uh, first,
I'd have to ask you

08:38.830 --> 08:41.420
if you're thinking about
harming yourself or others,

08:41.420 --> 08:43.000
because if so,
I'd have to refer you

08:43.000 --> 08:44.670
to someone
more qualified.

08:44.670 --> 08:45.790
Very natural,
Oliver.

08:47.460 --> 08:49.670
Katie: Okay, Dad's home.
Everybody, dinner.

08:49.670 --> 08:52.670
Can we just eat
in front of the TV for once?

08:52.670 --> 08:54.000
No.

08:54.000 --> 08:55.380
I want us all
to eat at the table.

08:55.380 --> 08:57.580
Family dinners
are important

08:57.580 --> 09:00.330
so we can keep track
of each other's lives.

09:00.330 --> 09:04.540
Because family is
where you should turn to first.

09:04.540 --> 09:06.420
Or you could turn
to a peer

09:06.420 --> 09:08.210
who's practicing
for an interview next week

09:08.210 --> 09:09.790
and has a script
that tells him what to say.

09:09.790 --> 09:11.330
Or a mother.

09:11.330 --> 09:15.080
A very cool, hip mother
who's easy to talk to.

09:16.080 --> 09:17.790
Who is
she talking about?

09:17.790 --> 09:18.880
Taylor: Herself.

09:18.880 --> 09:20.380
But it's
completely untrue.

09:20.380 --> 09:21.580
[ Bowl thuds ]

09:21.580 --> 09:24.920
I am a cool mother
who is easy to talk to.

09:24.920 --> 09:25.790
Everybody knows that.

09:25.790 --> 09:27.380
Greg: Hang on.

09:27.380 --> 09:28.790
Is this the result
of something you told me to do

09:28.790 --> 09:30.330
that I didn't handle?
No.

09:30.330 --> 09:32.670
That's all
I need to know.
But if
you need to know more,

09:32.670 --> 09:34.210
you should
go to Angela.

09:34.210 --> 09:35.790
I knew that's what
this was about!

09:35.790 --> 09:37.080
I'm going upstairs.

09:37.080 --> 09:38.620
Come on,
Trip.
No way.

09:38.620 --> 09:41.670
You two are not allowed
to be alone upstairs anymore.

09:41.670 --> 09:43.080
What?!
That's crazy!

09:43.080 --> 09:45.330
You are 17,
and you're gonna do as I say!

09:45.330 --> 09:46.080
I'm 18!

09:47.500 --> 09:48.710
Yeah.

09:50.330 --> 09:51.790
Well, I don't care
how old you are!

09:51.790 --> 09:54.580
My house, my rules!
Now sit down and eat!

09:54.580 --> 09:57.170
We are gonna have
a damn family dinner,

09:57.170 --> 10:00.210
and that's
the end of that!

10:00.210 --> 10:03.540
Do you know
what's going on?
I do...

10:03.540 --> 10:05.380
but I'd rather
talk about laser tag.

10:05.380 --> 10:09.920
♪♪

10:09.920 --> 10:12.040
Bill: Well, we tried to reason
with the lunch lady...

10:12.040 --> 10:13.170
But that
didn't work.

10:13.170 --> 10:14.540
So, unfortunately,

10:14.540 --> 10:16.330
we have to use public shaming
to get our point across.

10:16.330 --> 10:17.880
Thank you, guys,
for bagging up

10:17.880 --> 10:19.500
all the plastic waste
from lunch.

10:19.500 --> 10:20.580
Shoot.

10:20.580 --> 10:22.250
I think my retainer's
in one of these bags.

10:22.250 --> 10:24.880
Ugh.
Not you guys again.

10:24.880 --> 10:27.920
We wanted to show you how much
waste you create every day

10:27.920 --> 10:29.790
by using
disposable plates.

10:29.790 --> 10:32.000
All of this
from just one day?

10:33.250 --> 10:34.960
I was hoping
it would be a lot more.

10:34.960 --> 10:37.670
Ha-ha!
Bite me, Nature.

10:37.670 --> 10:39.500
[ Car door opens ]

10:39.500 --> 10:41.710
Ha-ha-ha!

10:41.710 --> 10:43.620
[ Engine starts ]

10:43.620 --> 10:47.380
[ Tires squeal ]

10:48.710 --> 10:50.210
[ Sighs ]

10:50.210 --> 10:52.460
I was hoping we wouldn't
have to resort to this.

10:52.460 --> 10:54.750
We're gonna have to
call in the big guns.

10:54.750 --> 10:56.000
"The Closer."

10:56.000 --> 10:57.790
"The Environmental
Assassin."

10:57.790 --> 11:00.330
Code name --
Mr. Green.

11:00.330 --> 11:01.920
My retainer!

11:05.960 --> 11:08.120
That's not mine.

11:08.120 --> 11:09.540
[ Retainer clatters ]

11:09.540 --> 11:16.710
♪♪

11:19.580 --> 11:21.960
"Hey, Snoop, I moved out.

11:21.960 --> 11:24.040
Since I'm not living
under your roof anymore,

11:24.040 --> 11:25.710
I guess I don't have to
follow your rules"?

11:25.710 --> 11:27.710
Oliver!

11:27.710 --> 11:29.790
[ Crumples paper ]

11:31.290 --> 11:32.670
Do you know
where Taylor went?

11:32.670 --> 11:34.460
I do, but I don't think
I should tell you

11:34.460 --> 11:36.330
because she came to me
in confidence,

11:36.330 --> 11:37.920
and confidentiality
is a bedrock principle

11:37.920 --> 11:38.960
at Teen Help Line.

11:40.000 --> 11:41.920
Where...

11:41.920 --> 11:43.170
is...

11:43.170 --> 11:44.620
your...

11:44.620 --> 11:46.580
sister?

11:46.580 --> 11:48.250
I feel like you're about to harm
yourself or someone else --

11:48.250 --> 11:50.210
Where is she?!
Angela's.
She went to Angela's.

11:50.210 --> 11:52.210
Gah.

11:52.210 --> 11:53.380
When you tell Taylor
I folded,

11:53.380 --> 11:55.710
make it sound like
I put up a good fight.

11:58.960 --> 12:02.210
First Taylor went behind my back
to get birth control,

12:02.210 --> 12:03.830
and now she moves in
with Angela.

12:03.830 --> 12:05.620
I don't understand why
you didn't tell me about this.

12:05.620 --> 12:07.330
Because I thought
I could handle it.

12:07.330 --> 12:09.540
Usually when I yell at Taylor,
she backs down.

12:09.540 --> 12:11.380
She didn't back down,
Greg,

12:11.380 --> 12:13.580
and I don't have
any other parenting tools.

12:13.580 --> 12:15.170
That's not true,
honey.

12:15.170 --> 12:16.790
You have public embarrassment,
sarcasm,

12:16.790 --> 12:17.960
and that thing

12:17.960 --> 12:19.540
where you sit on them
until they tell the truth.

12:19.540 --> 12:20.750
I thought
it was supposed to get easier

12:20.750 --> 12:21.830
as the kids got older.

12:21.830 --> 12:23.170
Me, too,
but now it's just

12:23.170 --> 12:24.830
bigger kids,
bigger problems.
Yeah.

12:24.830 --> 12:26.790
It used to be
choosing the right night light,

12:26.790 --> 12:29.000
and now I have
a 17-year-old daughter

12:29.000 --> 12:31.000
getting birth control
behind my back.

12:31.000 --> 12:32.960
Once again, she's 18.

12:32.960 --> 12:35.790
We should have thrown her
a better party.

12:37.380 --> 12:40.580
Listen, we're in
uncharted territory here.

12:40.580 --> 12:42.540
We're parenting
an adult.

12:42.540 --> 12:43.750
We need to adjust.

12:43.750 --> 12:46.330
I don't know
how to do that.

12:46.330 --> 12:48.330
I think the best thing to do
is wait.

12:48.330 --> 12:49.210
Let her come to us.

12:51.580 --> 12:53.670
Okay.

12:54.710 --> 12:57.210
[ Both sigh ]

12:58.460 --> 13:00.080
Screw this!
Let's go get her.

13:00.080 --> 13:02.120
You drive. I had half a glass
of port earlier.

13:02.620 --> 13:04.210
My baby girl.

13:04.210 --> 13:06.420
Taylor: [ Sighs ]
[ Door closes ]

13:08.250 --> 13:10.210
I had no idea
she was coming over.

13:10.210 --> 13:11.710
I told her
she couldn't stay,

13:11.710 --> 13:12.880
and I brought her
right back.

13:12.880 --> 13:14.460
This whole thing
has gone too far.

13:14.460 --> 13:15.710
The two of you
need to work it out.

13:15.710 --> 13:17.210
Thank you.

13:17.210 --> 13:19.080
But I am still
not talking to you.

13:19.080 --> 13:21.620
Still not
talking to you.

13:24.380 --> 13:25.750
Please tell me
you're still pure.

13:25.750 --> 13:27.420
Oh, my God, Dad!

13:27.420 --> 13:29.880
I'm glad you're back.

13:29.880 --> 13:30.830
I'm not talking
to you, either!

13:38.670 --> 13:40.580
I'm not sure what's happening
between you and Taylor,

13:40.580 --> 13:43.080
but I want you guys
to work this out.

13:43.080 --> 13:45.000
Reading all this stuff
about Teen Help Line

13:45.000 --> 13:47.210
makes me realize how many kids
don't have families to turn to.

13:49.290 --> 13:51.380
We're so lucky
to have each other.

13:53.120 --> 13:55.170
Oliver,
are you okay?
I don't know.

13:55.170 --> 13:56.330
What's happening?

13:56.330 --> 13:58.580
T-There's this tight feeling
in my chest.

13:58.580 --> 14:00.420
Honey...

14:00.420 --> 14:02.750
I think you're actually
feeling empathy.

14:02.750 --> 14:03.880
[ Burps ]

14:03.880 --> 14:05.710
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

14:05.710 --> 14:07.620
That's what that was.

14:07.620 --> 14:08.790
Whew!

14:08.790 --> 14:10.540
Anyway,
if she moves out again,

14:10.540 --> 14:12.330
I'm taking her room.

14:12.330 --> 14:18.290
♪♪

14:18.290 --> 14:19.540
Do you think
this will work?

14:19.540 --> 14:21.170
Hey, if anyone's a match
for the lunch lady,

14:21.170 --> 14:22.500
it's Mr. Green.
Mm.

14:22.500 --> 14:25.500
[ Brakes squeak ]

14:25.500 --> 14:27.790
♪♪

14:27.790 --> 14:29.040
♪♪

14:29.040 --> 14:31.250
[ Car alarm chirps ]

14:31.250 --> 14:38.380
♪♪

14:38.380 --> 14:39.620
Mr. Green:
Hello, boys.

14:39.620 --> 14:40.790
Oh.
Oh.

14:40.790 --> 14:42.420
Well, you've done
quite a good job here

14:42.420 --> 14:43.580
with your little posters
and everything.

14:43.580 --> 14:44.670
[ Chuckling ]
Thank you.

14:44.670 --> 14:46.000
Uh, but why don't you
sit back

14:46.000 --> 14:47.210
and let a professional
take over?

14:47.210 --> 14:48.710
We're so grateful
you're here.

14:48.710 --> 14:50.420
We've tried everything.
She just won't budge.

14:51.920 --> 14:53.620
Stand back.

14:53.620 --> 14:55.920
This...

14:55.920 --> 14:59.290
could get ugly.

14:59.290 --> 15:01.170
If you're talking about
your suit,

15:01.170 --> 15:02.330
you're right.

15:02.330 --> 15:03.670
You're going down,
lunch lady.

15:03.670 --> 15:05.750
Bring it, eco-nerd.

15:05.750 --> 15:07.750
I took the liberty

15:07.750 --> 15:10.000
of going through your trash
last night,

15:10.000 --> 15:12.460
and I found some stuff,
alright.

15:12.460 --> 15:14.080
Enough to charge you
with murder.

15:14.080 --> 15:15.960
Of a little lady
called...

15:15.960 --> 15:17.500
Mother Earth!

15:17.500 --> 15:18.460
Oh, that's good.
That's here.

15:18.460 --> 15:19.460
Yeah,
that's right.

15:19.460 --> 15:22.420
You got nothing on me,
recycopath.

15:24.620 --> 15:28.290
Exhibit A --

15:28.290 --> 15:32.620
you...
throw away batteries.

15:32.620 --> 15:34.460
Do you know what could happen
to you for doing this?

15:34.460 --> 15:37.750
Nothing?
Well, yeah...for now.

15:37.750 --> 15:39.210
But when
this becomes a law,

15:39.210 --> 15:41.170
you are in mild amounts
of trouble, lady.

15:41.170 --> 15:44.210
Got anything else?
Back to your trash.

15:44.210 --> 15:46.420
By the way,
the hair-removal industry

15:46.420 --> 15:48.250
thanks you
for your continued support.

15:48.250 --> 15:50.000
Exhibit B --

15:50.000 --> 15:54.540
you put cans
in the leaf bin.

15:54.540 --> 15:56.500
How do you live
with yourself?

15:56.500 --> 15:57.580
Quite well.

15:57.580 --> 15:59.830
And on Saturdays
and Sundays,

15:59.830 --> 16:02.000
butt naked
and drunk all day.

16:03.120 --> 16:04.420
Exhibit D...

16:04.420 --> 16:06.170
Wait,
didn't he skip exhibit C?

16:06.170 --> 16:08.040
Oh, for God's sake,
Greg, let the man work.

16:08.040 --> 16:09.120
Alright.

16:09.120 --> 16:10.500
You...

16:10.500 --> 16:13.420
put your magazines in
with the regular trash.

16:13.420 --> 16:15.380
Hey,
wait a minute.

16:15.380 --> 16:17.830
You subscribe
to "Cats Weekly"?
Yeah.

16:17.830 --> 16:19.580
I have two cats. And if you got
a problem with that,

16:19.580 --> 16:21.210
you can walk right out --
No, no, no, no.

16:21.210 --> 16:22.750
I'm a -- I'm a cat guy.
I love cats.

16:22.750 --> 16:24.380
What kinda --
What kinda cats you got?

16:24.380 --> 16:25.620
Calicos.

16:25.620 --> 16:28.080
Got to be a strong person
to have a Calico.

16:28.080 --> 16:29.790
You have to act like
you don't need 'em.

16:29.790 --> 16:30.830
That's the key.

16:30.830 --> 16:32.620
Yeah,
but you so do.

16:32.620 --> 16:35.250
Oh, yes.
More than air.

16:35.250 --> 16:36.460
What's happening?

16:36.460 --> 16:38.080
♪♪

16:38.080 --> 16:40.290
You have
the most beautiful eyes.

16:40.290 --> 16:43.420
You should see 'em when
I have my blue eye-shadow on.

16:43.420 --> 16:46.040
Hey, uh...

16:46.040 --> 16:47.250
can I take you
to lunch?

16:47.250 --> 16:49.500
Well, actually,
I'm a lunch lady,

16:49.500 --> 16:50.960
so that's pretty much
the only meal

16:50.960 --> 16:52.380
I'm not available for.

16:52.380 --> 16:54.000
But I am free
for dinner.

16:54.000 --> 16:55.710
So am I!

16:55.710 --> 16:57.880
I-I-I was gonna make a big deal
out of checking my calendar,

16:57.880 --> 17:00.380
but, uh, I'm a man
who likes cats, so...

17:00.380 --> 17:02.040
we both know
I'm free.

17:02.040 --> 17:03.210
[ Chuckles ]

17:03.210 --> 17:04.750
Wait,
are you...done?

17:04.750 --> 17:06.250
Is she gonna
recycle now?

17:06.250 --> 17:07.250
Who cares, man?!

17:07.250 --> 17:08.920
We both love cats!

17:08.920 --> 17:10.540
The same breed of cats!

17:10.540 --> 17:12.710
Franklin:
He's looking at her

17:12.710 --> 17:14.830
the same way
the FedEx guy looks at my mom.

17:16.420 --> 17:18.120
Okay,
we need to step in here.

17:18.120 --> 17:19.880
Excuse me,
lunch lady.

17:19.880 --> 17:22.170
You know why my mom
doesn't like to recycle?

17:23.000 --> 17:25.120
It's because
it's annoying.

17:25.120 --> 17:28.210
She says that washing the dishes
takes too much time.

17:28.210 --> 17:30.080
Is that
what you think?

17:30.080 --> 17:32.830
I'm tired of staying here
late at night doing it,

17:32.830 --> 17:35.620
and the school can't afford
to hire a dishwasher.

17:35.620 --> 17:36.710
How about this --

17:36.710 --> 17:38.210
if you stop
using plastic,

17:38.210 --> 17:40.000
I'll find someone
to help you.

17:42.500 --> 17:44.040
It's a deal.

17:44.040 --> 17:45.000
[ Chuckles ]

17:45.920 --> 17:47.290
[ Sighs ]

17:47.290 --> 17:48.580
We did it, buddy.
No.

17:48.580 --> 17:50.500
No,
Mother Earth did it.
Hmm.

17:50.500 --> 17:52.250
i think it's pretty clear
that I did it.

17:52.250 --> 17:53.540
Oh, well...
[ Gasps ]

17:53.540 --> 17:55.040
Oh, my God,
I am so late.

17:55.040 --> 17:56.250
I gotta get back
to Foot Locker.

17:56.250 --> 17:57.880
Robbie's gonna be
furious.

17:57.880 --> 18:02.080
♪♪

18:04.960 --> 18:06.920
Hey.

18:06.920 --> 18:07.920
Can I talk to you?

18:07.920 --> 18:09.250
Nope.

18:09.250 --> 18:11.170
I wasn't really asking.
I'm doing it anyway.

18:11.170 --> 18:12.880
[ Door closes ]

18:12.880 --> 18:14.920
[ Sighs ]

18:17.210 --> 18:21.330
I know that you are older
and doing...

18:21.330 --> 18:23.120
older things.

18:23.120 --> 18:25.330
I'll just push down

18:25.330 --> 18:28.960
all the feelings
I have about it and...

18:28.960 --> 18:30.750
take them out
on your brother and sister.

18:30.750 --> 18:32.540
[ Chuckles lightly ]

18:32.540 --> 18:35.670
[ Sighs ]

18:35.670 --> 18:38.420
It felt weird
not telling you about it,

18:38.420 --> 18:40.250
but then it felt weird
telling you about it.

18:40.250 --> 18:42.000
Eh --

18:42.000 --> 18:43.750
I just didn't know
what to do.

18:43.750 --> 18:45.380
I know.

18:45.380 --> 18:48.290
I'm trying
to figure it out, too.

18:48.290 --> 18:51.750
I'm so used to trying
to catch you before you fall...

18:51.750 --> 18:53.330
but you're 18 now.

18:55.040 --> 18:58.670
Good God, you're 18.

18:58.670 --> 19:01.710
How did that happen?

19:01.710 --> 19:03.000
[ Chuckles lightly ]

19:04.750 --> 19:06.790
Is it okay if I call Trip
and tell him to come over?

19:06.790 --> 19:08.580
Of course.

19:08.580 --> 19:11.210
[ Cellphone clicks,
dialing ]

19:11.210 --> 19:14.040
Can I speak to him for a second
so I can apologize?

19:14.040 --> 19:15.120
You're so great,
Mom.

19:15.120 --> 19:18.210
[ Chuckles ]

19:18.210 --> 19:20.000
[ Door opens ]

19:20.000 --> 19:21.420
Trip:
Hi, Mrs. A.

19:21.420 --> 19:24.000
If you ever so much as touch
my daughter without clothes on,

19:24.000 --> 19:25.830
I will hang you
with your own [bleep]

19:25.830 --> 19:27.580
Copy that, Mrs. A.

19:27.580 --> 19:33.080
♪♪

19:33.080 --> 19:34.460
Mm.

19:34.460 --> 19:36.250
And I shouldn't have
gotten mad at you.

19:36.250 --> 19:38.290
You were just
trying to help.

19:38.290 --> 19:39.710
I'm really sorry.

19:39.710 --> 19:41.330
Yeah.
Me, too.

19:41.330 --> 19:43.120
But this spoke to me
in a personal way.

19:43.120 --> 19:44.380
When I was
in high school,

19:44.380 --> 19:45.750
I had to keep it a secret
that I was gay

19:45.750 --> 19:48.210
and I always wished
I had someone to go to.

19:48.210 --> 19:49.920
I would have been
that person for you.

19:49.920 --> 19:51.500
Oh.
Yeah,
I would've, too.

19:51.500 --> 19:54.380
[ Laughs ] No.

19:54.380 --> 19:56.170
I would have told everybody,
and then I would have made up

19:56.170 --> 19:58.040
a very funny,
but offensive nickname.

19:58.040 --> 20:00.040
[ Chuckles ]

20:00.040 --> 20:02.540
It was
a different time!

20:02.540 --> 20:04.170
I miss it.
Ugh.

20:08.120 --> 20:10.880
I have a little bell
I want you to make me wear.

20:10.880 --> 20:12.380
You're wicked.

20:12.380 --> 20:15.920
I'm about to recycle
my breakfast.

20:15.920 --> 20:17.540
I just wish
Bill Doty was here

20:17.540 --> 20:19.120
to share in
our eco-victory.

20:19.120 --> 20:20.210
But he has his career.

20:22.380 --> 20:24.500
Is this job
a hobby to you?

20:24.500 --> 20:26.170
No, sir.

20:26.170 --> 20:28.330
Think you're so special,
you can take a 50-minute lunch?

20:28.330 --> 20:29.880
It won't happen again.

20:29.880 --> 20:32.920
Think this is fun for me,
riding you like this?

20:32.920 --> 20:34.790
Alright, I got a geometry final
tomorrow, alright?

20:34.790 --> 20:36.500
I don't need this,
Bill.

20:36.500 --> 20:39.080
Now get back in there
and push the New Balance.

20:39.080 --> 20:41.670
I could help you study
for your final. I have
a master's degree in --

20:41.670 --> 20:43.420
Why don't you sell
the damn shoes, Bill?!

20:43.420 --> 20:49.210
♪♪
